of%20Congress.%20No%20prior%20president%20has%20used%20IEEPA%20to%20levy%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20'national%20emergency'%20is%20that%20we%20have%20a%20trade%20deficit%20in%20goods%20%E2%80%94now%20that's%20not%20an%20emergency.%26quot%3B%20Jeffrey%20Schwab%2C%20Senior%20Counsel%20at%20the%20Liberty%20Justice%20Center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20a%20trade%20deficit%20basically%20for%2050%20years%2C%20so%20it%20can't%20be%20an%20emergency%2C%20and%20it%20certainly%20can't%20be%20unusual%20or%20extraordinary%20because%20it's%20common.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwab%20said%20that%20even%20if%20the%20use%20of%20the%20IEEPA%20ends%20up%20being%20justified%2C%20Congress%20is%20still%20not%20allowed%20to%20fully%20%26quot%3Boutsource%26quot%3B%20its%20tariff-making%20power%20to%20the%20president%2C%20because%20that%20would%20be%20unconstitutional%20under%20the%20nondelegation%20doctrine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20coming%20days%2C%20the%20Liberty%20Justice%20Center%20will%20seek%20injunctive%20relief%20to%20temporarily%20block%20tariffs%20while%20the%20case%20awaits%20a%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20exactly%20what%20we%20were%20concerned%20about%20when%20we%20fought%20the%20Revolutionary%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwab%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20Congress%20can%20delegate%20some%20authority%20for%20the%20President%20to%20issue%20tariffs%2C%20the%20President's%20interpretation%20of%20the%20IEEPA%20is%20so%20broad%20that%20it%20would%20give%20him%20almost%20unlimited%20authority%20to%20issue%20tariffs%20and%20set%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmall-businesses-suing-lawsuit-trump-liberation-day-tariffs-ieepa-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744668783000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67fd6bd4a466d2b74ab322a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%