es%20apps%20that%20share%20content%20with%20friends%20and%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20friend%20part%20has%20gone%20down%20quite%20a%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20testified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Facebook%20feed%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20turned%20into%20more%20of%20a%20broad%20discovery%20and%20entertainment%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%2C%20who%20was%20the%20first%20witness%20called%20after%20the%20trial%20opened%20on%20Monday%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20questioned%20for%20as%20long%20as%20seven%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20argues%20in%20its%20case%20that%20Meta%2C%20then%20called%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Facebook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20violated%20US%20competition%20laws%20when%20it%20acquired%20Instagram%20in%202012%20and%20WhatsApp%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20%241%20billion%20acquisition%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%2419%20billion%20acquisition%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-whatsapp-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20WhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20intended%20to%20box%20out%20competition%20and%20dominate%20the%20social%20media%20sphere%2C%20the%20FTC%20says.%20The%20government%20argues%20these%20acquisitions%20were%20part%20of%20Meta's%20%26quot%3Bbuy%20or%20bury%26quot%3B%20strategy%20to%20maintain%20market%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20said%20in%20court%20papers%20that%20Meta%20has%20maintained%20its%20monopoly%20position%20%26quot%3Bin%20significant%20part%26quot%3B%20by%20pursuing%20Zuckerberg's%20strategy%20outlined%20in%20an%20internal%202008%20email%20in%20which%20the%20CEO%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20better%20to%20buy%20than%20compete.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta%20has%20for%20many%20years%20reaped%20ma